What is a server?
- A server is a computer that provides sata or services to other computers via a network

What is the role of the domain name?
- The domain name allows for easy access of the website cause a text-based label is easier to recogize than an ip address

What type of DNS record www is in www.foobar.com?
- CNAME record

What is the role of the web server?
- The web server in this infrastructure hosts and manages the website

What is the role of the application server?
- The application server connects the systems, services and databases

What is the role of the database?
- a database manages user information so it can be easily accessed, managed and updated

What is the server using to communicate with the computer of the user requesting the website?
- The server communicates with  the website via a router

Issues with this infrastructure
- Since there is no load balancer, a single point of failure can occur. Also, the system is not scalable since we can't increase or decrease the number of servers without bringing down the whole application.